<SECOND>AM-BRF--Earth Rest Day,0152</SECOND>
<HEAD>Conservationists Call For An ``Earth Rest Day'' In The Philippines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An environmental group is urging
President Corazon Aquino to declare June 21 ``Earth Rest Day'' as
part of a worldwide effort to protect the environment.
   Maximo Kalaw, president of Haribon Foundation, said in a letter
to Mrs. Aquino that such a day would ``awaken our hearts, minds and
spirits to the plight of our endangered planet.''
   A government report recently said illegal logging and
slash-and-burn farming are destroying forests in the Philippines.
The document said the country's forest cover, once 54 percent, has
been reduced to 25 percent, leading to severe soil erosion in some
areas.
   The report also said that 18 species of wildlife are now listed
as endangered in the Phillipines and that another 25 are on the
threatened list.
   The United Nations Environment Program is coordinating ``Earth
Rest Day.''
