<FIRST>r i AM-Ivory     06-18 0125</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Ivory,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Large Haul of Ivory Products Seized in Hong Kong</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Customs officers on Sunday seized 448 tusks and
other ivory products worth $2.6 million that were to have been
smuggled to Japan, the Customs and Excise Department reported.
   Customs officers found the material during an inspection at the
cargo terminal at Hong Kong's airport, the department said in a
statement.
   On Friday, the Hong Kong government banned the import of raw
ivory in an effort to protect the African elephant.
   This month, the Customs Department formed a task force to stop
any illegal ivory imports or exports.
   The 10,874 pounds of ivory products were packed into eight
consignments that had been declared as watches for export, the
statement said.
</TEXT>
