<SECOND>AM-Saudi-No Beheading,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>Executioner's Sword Stayed Before Beheading a Murderer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIYADH, Saudi Arabia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man about to be beheaded for
killing a woman and her two children was saved when the woman's
husband forgave the killer just as the sword was about to be brought
down, a newspaper reported.
   ``Listen, I have forgiven you for the murder of my wife and
children, whom you will meet before God,'' Mohammed Yehia Ali Saeed
Faqihi, a Saudi national, said in front of the crowd, the daily
al-Riyadh reported. It said the incident occurred Friday.
   In accordance with Islamic law enforced in Saudi Arabia, the
death penalty against Mohammed Shera'ie was revoked, the newspaper
said.
   Shera'ie murdered the woman, her son and her daughter without any
apparent motive, the newspaper said.
   It said the execution was taking place in a public square after
the Friday Moslem sabbath prayers in southwest Jizzan, the paper
said.
   Islamic law prescribes beheading for convicted murderers, stoning
for adulterers and cutting off the hands of thieves.
