<FIRST>u a AM-NineKilled     06-18 0198</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Nine Killed,0203</SECOND>
<HEAD>9 Killed In Head-On Collision On Alligator Alley, FHP Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAPLES, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nine people burned to death in a head-on
collision involving a pickup truck and two cars Sunday afternoon,
state police said.
   The accident on state Route 84, known as Alligator Alley,
occurred at 4:40 p.m. about 44 miles east of Naples, said Florida
Highway Patrol Sgt. Craig Perkins in Fort Myers.
   ``We had seven people in a car that collided head-on with a
pickup truck carrying two people. They all burned to death,'' said
Perkins.
   Another car coming from behind and trying to avoid the accident
immediately sideswiped the wreckage, Perkins said, adding that the
two people in that car were not injured.
   ``We have people on the scene right now trying to clean up,''
Perkins said. ``It's raining out there right now. We don't know if
it was raining out there at the time of the accident.''
   The 100-mile, east-west highway through the Everglades, which
links Fort Lauderdale and Naples, was immediately closed following
the accident, Perkins said. The road is also part of Interstate 75.
   The identities of the the nine victims were not immediately
available, police said.
