<HEAD>Nissan Introduces Five-Speed Automatic Transmission</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nissan Motor Co. Ltd., Japan's second-largest
automaker, has introduced the world's first passenger car with an
electronically controlled five-speed automatic transmission, company
officials said.
   The transmission was mounted in the new Cedric and Gloria models,
